WEBVTT

00:04.873 --> 00:07.140
I mean, seriously,

00:07.209 --> 00:09.609
have you ever seen so many,
uh, whatchamacallits?

00:09.678 --> 00:11.244
Precious Moments.

00:11.313 --> 00:12.824
Those little statues
all over the place.

00:12.848 --> 00:15.248
That's what they're called.
Precious Moments?

00:15.317 --> 00:17.250
They're, like, a
really big thing...

00:17.319 --> 00:20.053
with cat ladies and my mother.

00:22.057 --> 00:23.390
Hey.

00:24.793 --> 00:27.460
Hey, there, pretty girl. Hi.
Boy.

00:27.529 --> 00:28.795
You sure?

00:28.864 --> 00:30.797
Uh, positive.

00:33.001 --> 00:35.468
Think he wants us to follow him.

00:35.537 --> 00:37.604
Okay, Lassie. Hey.

00:39.641 --> 00:42.242
Oh, I seriously cannot believe
that we are doing this.

00:42.310 --> 00:44.470
Ten to one we're being
punk'd by Sector Charlie.

00:44.494 --> 00:45.012
Yeah.

00:45.013 --> 00:47.347
Just let me go!

00:47.416 --> 00:49.015
You're not going anywhere!

00:49.084 --> 00:50.328
Let me go!
How many times I got to tell you?

00:50.352 --> 00:51.718
Yo! Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa!

00:51.787 --> 00:53.164
Hey! Hey! Hey, hey, hey!
Break it off.

00:53.188 --> 00:54.666
Break it-- Step away.
Yo, yo. All good. All good.

00:54.690 --> 00:56.189
Hey, what-what's going on?

00:56.258 --> 00:57.535
- Back away.
- We're just having a discussion, man.

00:57.559 --> 00:58.903
Discussion?
Yeah. Yeah. Yeah.

00:58.927 --> 01:00.412
You ever had a discussion before? Yo.
He hit me.

01:00.413 --> 01:01.829
Get this dog away from me. Get
this dog away from me right now.

01:01.853 --> 01:03.853
Hey.

01:04.498 --> 01:06.399
Cuff him.

01:09.371 --> 01:11.137
Unbelievable.

01:11.206 --> 01:13.406
This is all we got?
Sorry.

01:13.475 --> 01:15.875
We're standing in front
of a police precinct,

01:15.944 --> 01:16.712
and this is all we got?

01:16.736 --> 01:18.646
Yeah, I'm telling you,
that's all we got.

01:18.647 --> 01:20.880
Well... Well,
it's unacceptable.

01:20.949 --> 01:22.482
Why are you getting so hot?

01:22.551 --> 01:23.795
What do you mean?
The guy spray-painted

01:23.819 --> 01:26.119
my car!
<i>Our</i> car.

01:26.188 --> 01:28.299
You're gonna split hairs with me now.
I'm just saying.

01:28.323 --> 01:30.256
Well, I'm just saying
we look like idiots.

01:30.325 --> 01:31.891
I mean, we look
like the dopey cops

01:31.960 --> 01:33.526
in the <i>Smokey and</i>
<i>the Bandit</i> movies.

01:33.595 --> 01:36.529
Relax. It's probably just
some kid vandalizing.

01:36.598 --> 01:38.732
I'm sure no one
will even notice.

01:38.800 --> 01:40.100
Love the new
paint job, Reagan.

01:40.168 --> 01:42.669
Looking good, Danny Boy.

01:42.738 --> 01:45.105
You see that? We're
laughingstocks.

01:45.173 --> 01:46.740
Not we. You.

01:46.808 --> 01:48.508
Your car, remember?

01:48.577 --> 01:52.412
Way to look after
your partner, partner.

01:54.750 --> 01:57.417
Don't even say it.

01:59.755 --> 02:01.588
It was Kennedy.

02:01.656 --> 02:03.089
Pretty sure it was Roosevelt.

02:03.158 --> 02:04.190
Which one?

02:04.259 --> 02:05.325
Franklin D.

02:05.393 --> 02:07.761
No. JFK. 100%.

02:07.829 --> 02:09.429
- Google it. Morning, sir.
- Morning.

02:09.497 --> 02:11.164
Maybe you can help settle this.

02:11.233 --> 02:13.733
Which president coined the term
"first hundred days"?

02:13.802 --> 02:16.336
FDR.
I say JFK.

02:16.404 --> 02:20.006
FDR gave an address
in July of 1933.

02:20.075 --> 02:22.075
Since then it's
been the benchmark.

02:23.078 --> 02:24.177
Thank you.

02:24.246 --> 02:26.112
This about the <i>Times?</i>

02:26.181 --> 02:27.258
We've held them off
for about as long

02:27.282 --> 02:28.392
as we're gonna get away with.

02:28.416 --> 02:31.184
The mayor's office
has been hounding me 24-7.

02:31.253 --> 02:33.820
This hounding in
reference to anything

02:33.889 --> 02:36.322
about my wanting more cops?

02:36.391 --> 02:38.792
No, it's about you
talking to the <i>Times</i>

02:38.860 --> 02:41.828
about his first 100 days,
in a positive way.

02:41.897 --> 02:47.934
Then let them howl.

02:48.003 --> 02:51.805
I prefer "mutually
beneficial exchange."

02:51.873 --> 02:55.275
Seriously?
It's the only language he knows.

02:55.343 --> 02:57.310
I'm not quite sure
how to communicate that.

02:57.379 --> 03:00.079
Well, then, I will. Tomorrow.

03:00.148 --> 03:01.526
Okay, let's not get
ahead of ourselves.

03:01.550 --> 03:03.983
This <i>Times</i> hundred-day thing,
when's it run?

03:04.052 --> 03:06.586
Next weekend.
The cover of the magazine.

03:06.655 --> 03:09.923
Then get it done today
or step off it.

03:16.298 --> 03:19.499
Well, what do you know?

03:19.568 --> 03:20.978
I used to have a daughter
named Nicky

03:21.002 --> 03:22.168
who looked just like you.

03:22.237 --> 03:24.604
Hi, Mom. I know it's been
a while since I called.

03:24.673 --> 03:26.239
Almost a week.

03:26.308 --> 03:28.341
You know, in the real world,

03:28.410 --> 03:30.176
that's not actually
a very long time.

03:30.245 --> 03:33.146
Oh, really? Well, when you carry
another living being

03:33.215 --> 03:35.515
inside of you for nine months,

03:35.584 --> 03:36.883
then you can tell me that.

03:36.952 --> 03:38.451
Actually, wait, don't.

03:38.520 --> 03:40.787
Wait, that's not why
you're calling.

03:40.856 --> 03:42.133
Tell me that's not
why you're calling.

03:42.157 --> 03:43.456
Relax, Mom.

03:43.525 --> 03:45.925
I'm not pregnant.
I just called to say hi.

03:45.994 --> 03:48.661
Well, you just made my day.

03:48.730 --> 03:50.296
You look tired.
Long day?

03:50.365 --> 03:52.098
Thank you. Yes.

03:52.167 --> 03:53.444
You should come out here
and visit.

03:53.468 --> 03:55.501
Do some California dreaming
with me.

03:55.570 --> 03:57.170
I should.

03:57.239 --> 03:58.738
But you won't.

03:58.807 --> 04:00.673
Well, you should see my desk.

04:00.742 --> 04:02.787
Ugh, I'm so sorry,
that's my boss on the other line.

04:02.811 --> 04:05.311
I'll call you right back, okay?
Wait. Wait, Nick. Nick...

04:05.380 --> 04:06.446
Bye.
Nick.

